types.description:
Represents a CQL `date` as a string.
This is a date without a time-zone in the ISO-8601 calendar system.
Example: "2020-10-21".A date can also be input as a 32-bit, positive numeric literal, which will be
interpreted as a number of days, where the epoch is in the middle of the range

types.description:

This is an IP address in IPv4 or IPv6 format.
Examples: "127.0.0.1", "::1"
If you don't provide a numerical address, it will be resolved on the server.

types.name: Time
types.description:
Represents a CQL `time` as a string.
This is a time without a time-zone in the ISO-8601 calendar system.Example: "10:15:30.123456789"
A time can also be input as a numeric literal, which will be interpreted
as a number of nanoseconds since midnight.

types.name: TimeUuid
types.description:
Represents a CQL `timeuuid` as a string.
Example: "fe86cad0-1965-11eb-84e6-ab660d2e8c9e"

types.name: Timestamp
types.description:
Represents a CQL `timestamp` as a string.
This is an instantaneous point on the time-line.
This type supports many different string representations, see https://docs.datastax.com/en/cql-oss/3.x/cql/cql_reference/timestamp_type_r.html
A timestamp can also be input as a numeric literal, which will be interpreted
as a number of milliseconds since the epoch (1970-01-01 UTC at midnight).
Examples: "2011-02-03 04:05+0000", 1296705900000
String literals that do not include any time zone information will be
interpreted using the server's default time zone.

fields.name: directives

types.name: __TypeKind
types.description: An enum describing what kind of type a given __Type is

enumValues.name: SCALAR
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a scalar.

enumValues.name: OBJECT
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an object. `fields` and `interfaces` are valid fields.

enumValues.name: INTERFACE
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an interface. `fields` and `possibleTypes` are valid fields.

enumValues.name: UNION
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a union. `possibleTypes` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: ENUM
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an enum. `enumValues` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: INPUT_OBJECT
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an input object. `inputFields` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: LIST
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a list. `ofType` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: NON_NULL
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a non-null. `ofType` is a valid field.

directives.name: include
directives.description: Directs the executor to include this field or fragment only when the `if` argument is true

directives.name: skip
directives.description: Directs the executor to skip this field or fragment when the `if`'argument is true.

directives.name: atomic
directives.description: Instructs the server to apply the mutations in a LOGGED batch

directives.name: deprecated
directives.description: Marks the field or enum value as deprecated
